sentence: Procter & Gamble Co. (Symbol: PG) has been named to the Dividend Channel ''S.A.F.E.

25'' list, signifying a stock with above-average ''DividendRank'' statistics including a strong 3.2% yield, as well as a superb track record of at least two decades of dividend growth, according to the most recent ''DividendRank'' report.

According to the ETF Finder at ETF Channel , Procter & Gamble Co. is a member of the iShares S&P 1500 Index ETF ( ITOT ), and is also an underlying holding representing 1.17% of the SPDR S&P Dividend ETF ( SDY ), which holds $177,183,712 worth of PG shares.
Procter & Gamble Co. (Symbol: PG) made the "Dividend Channel S.A.F.E.
25" list because of these qualities: S .
Solid return - hefty yield and strong DividendRank characteristics; A.
Accelerating amount - consistent dividend increases over time; F .
Flawless history - never a missed or lowered dividend; E. Enduring - at least two decades of dividend payments.
The annualized dividend paid by Procter & Gamble Co. is $2.678/share, currently paid in quarterly installments, and its most recent dividend ex-date was on 01/18/2017.
